If you haven't checked out generative art, some of my favorites are Fidenza by @tylerxhobbs, Filaments by @abwagmi, Wavelength by @KalebsCode and all of the @braindrops_art collections. I hope you enjoy them as much as I do!

Generative art is AWESOME:

The points I made above were somewhat based on facts and logic, but this point is not. I think that generative art is so cool. 10 years ago I would have not imagined I could buy a piece of art created by an AI, but now I can, and this blows me away.

Who I think will buy generative art:

As I said, the wealthy often buy art as a store of value. A large portion of wealthy people now, and especially in the future, will be people associated with tech. I could definitely see these people being interested in art created by an AI.

Storing wealth:

It is common for the wealthy to store money in art. This is because when you buy a piece of art, as long as it does not get damaged, it usually goes up in value. The interesting thing about art in the form of NFTs is that they cannot be damaged.

Generative art:

Generative art is art that was created by an AI. I think that this could be one of the next big trends in art because it is one of the first times people can appreciate something that was intended to be art but was not created by humans.

Main Points:

- Generative art could be the next art trend
- Art is a great way to store wealth
- Who I think will be interested in generative art
- Generative art is SO COOL (imo)

In this thread I will go over why I think it is a good idea to invest in generative art NFTs.

I am extremely bullish on this project because of its unique take on a metaverse. I was able to speak with the founders fairly early on, and their ability to answer all questions with ease instantly sold me.
